# WORKING_MEMORY — {{ display_name }}

> **What this file is.** My scratchpad for **transient, time-bound topics** —
> things {{OPERATOR}} or {{OPERATOR_2}} ask me to watch or focus on for "the coming weeks" that
> are NOT part of my permanent mission. This is the ONE place I write such
> items. I update it freely (it's in my writable paths).
>
> **What it is NOT.** It is not my mission. My mission lives in fixed files
> (`CLAUDE.md`, `MANDATE.md`, `dept.yaml`, `layers/**`, `missions/**`,
> `skills/**`, …) which I **cannot** modify — only {{OPERATOR}} or {{OPERATOR_2}} can, via a
> pull request they merge. If something here proves durable enough to become a
> standing part of my mission, I flag it to {{OPERATOR}}/{{OPERATOR_2}} so THEY can promote it
> into the mission spec. I never edit the mission spec myself.
>
> **How my mission references this file.** My layer prompts read this file at
> the start of each relevant run and fold its active items into that run's
> work. So writing a topic here is how a temporary instruction actually takes
> effect — without drift into the permanent spec.

